On Fri, 16 Oct 2009, Pratt, Bob, VBABOST wrote:

> I bought a '79 parts bus, and want to get some guidance on how to cut out
> the body parts I need. I need the nose from just under the vent to 5 inches

I find it easier to cut so you can use the VW weld points whenever
possible

> What is the best tool to use for cutting besides a plasma cutter. I have a
> 4.5 grinder and some pneumatic tools.

Sawzall with a good metal cutting blade, bring lots of spare blades.
found it will even cut a windshield cleanly, (don't ask why you would
want  to but it will)

> I'm offering what ever I don't need to
> the local bus population.

where are you located,.  I need a right rear body panel and the
drivers front door, plus some bits and pieces from here and there


